{"parse":{"title":"Monument to Donizetti, Bergamo","pageid":50482500,"revid":824083728,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG/220px-Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"132\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG/330px-Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG/440px-Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"4694\" data-file-height=\"2814\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bergamo_Donizetti.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Monument to Donizetti, Bergamo</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Monument to Donizetti</b> by <a href=\"/wiki/Francesco_Jerace\" title=\"Francesco Jerace\">Francesco Jerace</a> is located in a public garden in Piazza Cavour, adjacent to the <a href=\"/wiki/Teatro_Donizetti\" title=\"Teatro Donizetti\">Teatro Donizetti</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Bergamo\" title=\"Bergamo\">Bergamo</a>. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Monument_to_Donizetti,_Bergamo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The monument was inaugurated in 1897, at the centenary of his birth and in his birthplace, and commemorates the opera composer <a href=\"/wiki/Gaetano_Donizetti\" title=\"Gaetano Donizetti\">Gaetano Donizetti</a>. Jerace was elected via a competition to complete the monument. The statuary group is atop a plain plinth engraved only with the composers name. The monument is surrounded by a Basin. Atop, Donizetti sits, realistically depicted, and  bound to present world, in the corner of a curved bench. A short distance away stands the lyrical muse, <a href=\"/wiki/Melpomene\" title=\"Melpomene\">Melpomene</a>, strumming her lyre. The artist, with eyes closed, listens to his inspiration. The statue mixes both realism and the allegory to classical mythology; also expressing the sense that the artists communicates with a superior realm.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Donizetti's funereal monument in Bergamo, se up in 1856 features a mournful lyrical muse.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Monument_to_Donizetti,_Bergamo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.scultura-italiana.com/Biografie/Jerace.htm\">Scultura Italiana</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20160602230118/http://www.scultura-italiana.com/Biografie/Jerace.htm\">Archived</a> 2016-06-02 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>., biography.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=-OMNAAAAYAAJ\">The Italy of the Italians</a>, by Helen Zimmern, pp. 130\u2013131.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span id=\"coordinates\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a>: <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Monument_to_Donizetti,_Bergamo&amp;params=45.69545_N_9.67171_E_type:landmark_region:IT\"><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">45\u00b041\u203244\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">9\u00b040\u203218\u2033E</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">45.69545\u00b0N 9.67171\u00b0E</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">45.69545; 9.67171</span></span></span></a></span></span></span>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1272\nCached time: 20180909123201\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.076 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.107 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 173/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 2688/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 201/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 992/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 1/400\nLua time usage: 0.032/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 947 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   87.477      1 -total\n 61.97%   54.213      1 Template:Reflist\n 39.60%   34.638      1 Template:Webarchive\n 37.91%   33.167      1 Template:Coord\n  9.28%    8.120      2 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache: